narratives.question_text: Please rate and comment on the following aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Workload
comments: Andy adjusted workload accordingly when we fell behind in class, and each assignment had a clear purpose. The final project had defined learning objectives and was an appropriate challenge that capped off our semester.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Organization.Comments:
comments: The syllabus is poorly formatted - some simple bullets for assignments and objectives would go a long way, as well as clear demarcation of deadlines (is the assignment due for the class it's listed under or the following class?). Otherwise, the progression was clear, and though the tone was conversational, I always knew what the focus was and he was good at keeping us on track.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: the Instructor.Comments:
comments: Andy is a busy man, but clearly dedicated to us and the class. Even in the midst of his job transition, this class was obviously a priority for him, and I never felt that he was out of touch. Plus, he has so much great experience, and thus tons of excellent examples that illustrate the material clearly.

narratives.question_text: Please comment on: Visitors, if any
comments: Fran Kumin's visit, I suspect, will improve in future years. She's a great person to have met, and very knowledgeable; I just think that she didn't pace her presentation out very well with all the details she wanted to share. (I think she got through 30% of the material she planned to cover.) In short - I wanted more time with her! Perhaps she can have a whole class session instead of half?

narratives.question_text: Please comment on all aspects of your experience in this course or module regarding: Your Learning.Comments:
comments: I learned a lot about cultivating relationships with diverse donors, and perhaps above all I learned about the value of listening to their needs rather than just presenting my own. A major lesson I'll carry with me! I am very glad to have been given the proper vocabulary for this increasingly important area of the profession.
